    "notes": [
      {
        "category": "summary",
        "text": "An update is available for toolbox.\nThis update affects Rocky Linux 9.\nA Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE list",
        "title": "Topic"
      },
      {
        "category": "description",
        "text": "The toolbox container image can be used with Toolbox to obtain Rocky Linux based containerized command line environments to aid with development and software testing. Toolbox is built on top of Podman and other standard container technologies from OCI.\n\nThis updates the toolbox image in the Rocky Enterprise Software Foundation container registry.\n\nTo pull this container image, run one of the following commands:\n\n    podman pull registry.redhat.io/toolbox (authenticated)\n    podman pull registry.access.redhat.com/ubi9/toolbox (unauthenticated)\n\nThis advisory is provided by Ctrl IQ, Inc for Rocky Linux systems. For more information about CIQ security practices, visit https://ciq.com/security.",
        "title": "Description"
      }
    ],
